2 Certificate (legacy)","anchor":"p12-Certificate-legacy"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you may utilize Apple’s older authentication scheme (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"text":" SSL certificates). Unlike the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"text":" solution described above, these certificates automatically expire every year and will require you to regenerate and re-upload them. Braze will send you email reminders as the certificate approaches expiration to help your notifications continue uninterrupted, but because this is a manual process we recommend utilizing the above-described ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"text":" authentication scheme instead. However, if you still wish to, you may configure and upload ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"type":"text","text":" certificates as described here:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"Step-1-Generate-Certificate-Signing-Request","text":"Step 1: Generate Certificate Signing Request"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/ios\/manage\/overview\/index.action"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Identifiers"}]},{"type":"text","text":" in the left sidebar and filter "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"App Ids"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" using the button on the right of the page "},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-identifiers-app-ids.png"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select your application."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enable push notifications by checking the checkbox then click "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Edit"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"apns-certificate-app-id-config.png","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click Create Certificate under the Production SSL Certificate ","type":"text"},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-modal.png"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Production SSL Certificate","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" are suitable for App Store and TestFlight builds. Use a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Development SSL Certificate","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" to for development builds."}]}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Follow the instructions from the SSL certificate assistant.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must update your provisioning profile for the app after you create your SSL certificates. A simple “Refresh” in the organizer will accomplish this."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Step-2-Export-Certificate","level":4,"text":"Step 2: Export Certificate","type":"heading"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Download the production push certificate that you just created and open it with the Keychain Access application.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Keychain Access, click on My Certificates and locate your push certificate."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Export it as a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"text":" file and use a temporary, unsecure password (you will need this password when uploading your certificate to Braze).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineCont